WEBVTT

00:09.540 --> 00:14.500
In the 17th century, there was only
one place to see and be seen.

00:14.500 --> 00:17.420
The Palace of Versailles.

00:17.420 --> 00:20.580
The greatest legacy of Louis XIV.

00:20.580 --> 00:21.980
The Sun King.

00:23.180 --> 00:28.340
Louis XIV spent a whopping 72 years
on the throne.

00:28.340 --> 00:32.659
During his reign, he turned France
from a country racked by civil war,

00:32.659 --> 00:36.180
its dukes and nobles constantly at
each other's throats,

00:36.180 --> 00:39.820
into the most glorious and powerful
state in Europe.

00:39.820 --> 00:42.460
And he came up with a way of running
a royal court

00:42.460 --> 00:45.140
that's never been beaten.

00:45.140 --> 00:46.940
Key to his success was this -

00:46.940 --> 00:48.980
his Palace of Versailles.

00:50.940 --> 00:56.220
I'm Lucy Worsley, chief curator at
Britain's Historic Royal Palaces.

00:56.220 --> 00:59.980
And I'm Helen Castor, a historian
with an unhealthy interest

00:59.980 --> 01:02.300
in court politics and intrigue.

01:03.700 --> 01:07.660
Together, we're taking a look at
the new French-produced drama

01:07.660 --> 01:10.740
being shown on the BBC.

01:10.740 --> 01:14.060
It's set during the building of
Versailles.

01:14.060 --> 01:18.940
This was a world where life revolved
around endless court rituals.

01:18.940 --> 01:23.340
Where fortunes rose and fell
with the latest fashions.

01:23.340 --> 01:28.380
And where the quickest way to royal
favour was through the king's
bedchamber.

01:28.380 --> 01:29.900
Take it off.

01:29.900 --> 01:33.300
Behind the facade,
Louis XIV's survival

01:33.300 --> 01:35.900
depended on his creation of
Versailles.

01:36.940 --> 01:39.980
It was his power base,
his safe house

01:39.980 --> 01:44.860
and the gilded cage in which
he trapped his enemies.

01:44.860 --> 01:46.860
Never before had a king

01:46.860 --> 01:50.340
and his entire court lived together
in a single palace.

01:50.340 --> 01:54.260
This was a new type of building
for a new type of ruler.

01:54.260 --> 01:58.700
It was a huge risk. It could all
have gone horribly wrong.

01:58.700 --> 02:01.940
But if anybody could pull it off,
it was Louis XIV.

